# Walkthrough - Premium Inventory & Billing

I have completed the premium redesign for both the **Manage Products** and **Generate Bill** pages, ensuring a unified, modern, and high-performance user experience.

## Visual & Functional Upgrades

### 1. Unified Premium Styling
- **Glassmorphism**: Applied consistent glass backgrounds, soft borders, and backdrop blurs across the entire application.
- **Improved Visibility**: Fixed "invisible" input fields and dropdown options. No more white-on-white text; all inputs now have a subtle background and clear borders.
- **Refined Table Design**: Both product and billing tables now feature hover effects, row separation, and prominent pricing tags.

### 2. Billing Refinements (Generate Bill)
- **Two-Column Layout**: A dedicated sidebar for the **Bill Summary** makes it easier to track totals and balances while adding items.
- **Enhanced Quantity (QTY) Inputs**: Increased the width of the QTY box to 140px for better readability and easier selection.
- **Robust "Vanish Zero" Logic**: Numerical fields (Quantity, Price, Discount, Paid Today) now automatically clear the `0` value on focus, making it effortless to enter new data.
- **Auto-Fill Pricing**: Selecting or typing a recognized product name automatically pulls the default price from your inventory.

### 3. Dedicated Product Inventory
- **Manage Products Tab**: A new, dedicated section for CRUD operations on products, keeping your billing interface clean.
- **Consistently Premium**: Mirroring the design of the billing page for a cohesive "Dashboard" experience.

## Bug Fixes
- **Dropdown Visibility**: Fixed a critical issue where vendor selection options were white-on-white. They are now dark-themed and fully readable.
- **Focus States**: Improved input focus styling with an accent-color glow for better accessibility.

